Thank you for providing that information. Based on the details you've shared, I would recommend the following design for your study arms:

Study Arm 1: Experimental: MentorPRO - 12 sessions with a mentor
Participant Group/Arm: Students who are randomly assigned to the experimental group will have the opportunity to connect with a mentor for 12 sessions over 12 weeks using the MentorPRO mobile application.
Intervention/Treatment: Behavioral - MentorPRO
- The app features a dashboard for goal setting, tracking progress, and accessing educational resources or activities;
- A personalized relationship with a mentor offering accountability checks, progress-tracking reports, and personalized feedback;
- An embedded peer cohort, which offers social integration with other students going through the same program;
- An education/resources library will be accessible to all students via the app, regardless of group assignment.
- 12 sessions with a mentor, averaging 30 minutes in length.

